==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mexicanize
<hw>Mex"i*can*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. v. t.</pos> <def>To
cause to be like the Mexicans, or their country.</def> <note>At one time
this word referred to frequent revolutions of government, considered
characteristic of Mexican politics.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mexicanize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mexicanize
<hw>Mex"i*can*ize</hw>, <pos>prop. v. i.</pos> <def>To become like the
Mexicans, or their country or government.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meyne</ent>⟦br⟧
